{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ea63d142-c1bd-4911-a9b1-eb77482deb75","content":"**MSTest.Sdk 4.0+ dropped VSTest as the default runner.** Starting with v4.0.0, the SDK defaults to **Microsoft.Testing.Platform** only — it no longer generates a VSTest-compatible test host. That's why `vstest.console` can't discover your tests.\n\nYou have two options:\n\n### Option 1 — Switch your CI to `dotnet test` (recommended)\nNo project changes needed. Replace `vstest.console` with:\n```\ndotnet test TestProject.csproj\n```\n\n### Option 2 — Re-enable VSTest compatibility\nAdd this to your `.csproj`:\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <EnableMSTestRunner>false</EnableMSTestRunner>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\nThis restores the classic VSTest adapter so `vstest.console` works again, but you lose the new platform benefits (faster startup, better parallelism, `.exe` host).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"39316b01-86f9-4c88-bb17-f486fd42b9e2","outputTokens":221,"requestId":"7028:3A9384:48708D:54DFB8:69F2C337"},"id":"34c25a80-7c86-4543-ad28-c20828d60f7b","timestamp":"2026-04-30T02:49:33.843Z","parentId":"ac039682-db47-4bb6-a556-3a779ebc560d"}
